                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">Duplicate”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Curacao</placeName>\n                                        <date>October 25<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1848</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I received your sundry favors <date>2nd<lb/>\n                                                  March</date> &amp; <date>2<hi rend=\"sup\">nd</hi>\n                                                  May</date>, &amp; <date>21<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi>\n                                                  August</date>, together with all the missing<lb/>\n                                        occidents, and a letter from <persName>Mr. J. J.\n                                                  Seixas</persName> explaining the<lb/> detentions\n                                        of those letters and books having been occasioned<lb/> by\n                                        the negligence of our <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                                        agents, which I regret<lb/> as it has been the cause of my\n                                                  <sic>loosing</sic> many subscribers, I was<lb/>\n                                        reduced to 5, but since the books have arrived I have got 2\n                                        more<lb/> thus now I have 7 subscribers. In my last I\n                                        informed you<lb/> of my having disposed of one Sett of\n                                        Prayer Books, since<lb/> which tho we have passed all the\n                                        holidays which is the time to sell<lb/> I have not been able\n                                        to dispose of a single Sett, they all com=<lb/>plain the\n                                        books are too large and heavy. So much so that I<lb/> have\n                                        orders for three Setts if printed on thin paper like your\n                                        Daily<lb/> Services, and as they fear you will not have them\n                                        bound as<lb/> they wish, <hi rend=\"underline\">that is to say\n                                                  one of the persons</hi>, he requests you will<lb/>\n                                        send him out <hi rend=\"underline\">an unbound Sett</hi> if on\n                                        thin paper, his object is to<lb/> cut off the margins as\n                                        much as possible, and then have<lb/> them bound in smaller\n                                        vols. according to his own taste<lb/> they being for a very\n                                        young lady who could not well<lb/> hold <sic>ones</sic> of\n                                        these books in her hands the time she should<lb/> in\n                                        consequence of the weight, the other two setts you will<lb/>\n                                        please send according to the order enclosed, all three<lb/>\n                                        Setts are bespoken consequently they must be</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
