              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>according to the order, and those you cant fulfill (if<lb/> any)\n                                        according to the order do not send at all as I<lb/> am\n                                        exposed to receive them on my hands, you would<lb/> do well\n                                        also to put up a few setts more for me to sell<lb/> with at\n                                        least the kipur books divided in two or three, and<lb/>\n                                        always on thin paper, as those heavy books will not\n                                        sell.<lb/> the <placeName>west India</placeName> ladies will\n                                        not use them, the English<lb/> editions being so much\n                                        smaller or lighter. I am very<lb/> much obliged to you for\n                                        the notice you took of my dear<lb/> wife's death. The\n                                        sentiments expressed being your own<lb/> I am doubly\n                                        thankful. I would surmise in the price<lb/> of the books you\n                                        charge them 5 per cent over your price as<lb/> here 5 franc\n                                        pieces pay for Dollars, and if you require re=<lb/>mittance\n                                        in that specie you will have to <sic>loose</sic> the\n                                        dif=<lb/>-ference, however you do not mention any thing of\n                                        that<lb/> in yr letter as I may perhaps have to shew it to\n                                        them.</p>\n                              <p>In your kind favor of <date>2<hi rend=\"sup\">nd</hi> May.</date> I\n                                        perceive w/ much<lb/> pleasure your promise to send my\n                                        sister <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Lindo</persName> a number of the\n                                        Occident I have written her<lb/> to that effect, and have\n                                        requested her to apply to your<lb/> agents in\n                                                  <placeName>London</placeName>, if she does not\n                                        hear from them,<lb/> with the sett of prayer Books here in\n                                        ordered to be<lb/> sent unbound please send (on same sort\n                                        paper &amp; same <add>?</add>)<lb/> a Sett of Pentateuch\n                                        unbound, as the person wishes to<lb/> have them, forming one\n                                        complete Sett all bound alike<lb/> and all printed alike. I\n                                        will copy below this the<lb/> order he has given me in his\n                                        own words to avoid mis=<lb/>takes. Hoping you have passed\n                                        pleasantly the holidays &amp; that you may<lb/> see many\n                                        happy returns of them. I am yr Sincere friend.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
