          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/canvas/p3/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>PS. In your favor of <date>2<hi rend=\"sup\">nd</hi>: March</date>,\n                                        you say the Books I<lb/> ordered for <placeName>Pto\n                                                  Cabello</placeName> will go by the next\n                                        packet,<lb/> now I do not recollect having ordered any\n                                        Books<lb/> for <placeName>Pto Cabo.</placeName>, or any\n                                        where else, if you have sent<lb/> any please let me\n                                        know.—</p>\n                              <p><hi rend=\"underline\">Copy</hi>: One Sett Prayer Books</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">One Ditto Pentateuch all printed on thin<lb/>\n                                        paper, to be unbound, the person wants to get<lb/> them\n                                        bound here, that he may divide them to his liking<lb/> and\n                                        his motive for wishing thin paper's because<lb/> he wanted\n                                        them for his young daughter, consequently<lb/> he wants them\n                                        light, if they cant be sent according<lb/> to his\n                                                  <sic>desine</sic> do not send them.</p>\n                              <p><date>Decr. 8.</date> Dr Sir.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">The foregoing is duplicate of my last\n                                        respects<lb/> since which I have recd. yr. favors <date>3\n                                                  Oct.</date> &amp; <date>31<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                                                  >st</hi></date> and the<lb/> Books correct as per\n                                        your notes.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr. Dacosta</persName> left this morning\n                                        for <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> to<lb/> fetch out his\n                                        sister who is coming out from\n                                        <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> to join him here,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am afraid you will never see the money if<lb/>\n                                        the books <persName>Mr. Lobo</persName> of <placeName>Puerto\n                                                  Cavello</placeName> had from you<lb/> ask is not\n                                        the best paymaster, I hope tho' it<lb/> will prove\n                                        otherwise.—wishing you well, and<lb/> with respect I am Dr\n                                        Sir yrs. Truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                                        <persName>O U Dacosta</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">pp. <persName role=\"author\"><hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >John E. Price</hi></persName></p>\n                              <p>Encld. A letter recd for you</p>\n                              <p>frm. <placeName>Suriname</placeName>.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32r3pd2z/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
